1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 12.1-41 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the implementation of operational guidelines and training for law
3 enforcement officers and state's attorneys addressing the crimes of human trafficking,
4 prostitution, and the commercial exploitation of children.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 12.1-41 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Law enforcement guidelines - Training - Prevention .
9 1. Each law enforcement agency shall develop and implement specific operational
10 guidelines for handling a crime involving human trafficking, prostitution, or commercial
11 exploitation of children.
12 a. The guidelines must include procedures for:
13 (1) Conducting a criminal investigation;
14 (2) Arresting a suspect;
15 (3) Assisting a victim;
16 (4) Connecting a victim with services; and
17 (5) Any additional procedures necessary to carry out this chapter.
18 b. The attorney general shall assist a law enforcement agency in the development
19 and implementation of procedures.
20 2. The peace officer standards and training board shall establish a training and education
21 program for law enforcement officers and state's attorneys on detecting, responding
22 to, and investigating a crime involving human trafficking, prostitution, or commercial
23 exploitation of children.
24 a. The training must include information on community resources for a victim.
